The paper discusses the lack of tools for hardware reverse engineering and proposes the use of cognitive obfuscation based on psychological insights. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer security (cs.CR), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), software engineering (cs.SE), architecture (cs.AR), and systems and control (cs.SY).
